{"lemma":"أَشْجَعَيْ","slug":"أَشْجَعَيْ","root":"ش.ج.ع","root_slug":"ش-ج-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ج-ع","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":0},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n21771"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n21771","headword_ar":"اَشْجَعُ","root":"$jE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajoEaA='u","text_ar":"شَجْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ujaAEN","text_ar":"شُجَاعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labuw^apN $ajoEaA='u","text_ar":"لَبُوَةٌ شَجْعَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bold lioness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Applied to a man, accord. to some, it signifies, (S,) or it signifies also, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In whom is lightness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsteadiness, like what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hawajN","text_ar":"هَوَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of his strength."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ajiEN","text_ar":"شَجِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mad;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessed by a devil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) Lth says that, applied to a man, it signifies one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is as though there were in him madness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diabolical possession;"},{"kind":"text","text":"but Az says that this is a mistake; for, were this its meaning, the poets would not have used it in praise. (TA, in another part of the art.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Tall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, Msb, K:) and so the fem. applied to a woman. (IDrd, Msb.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bulky; big-bodied;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stout:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"youthful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of youthful vigour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, S, K.) ―         -b7-  It is said in the K that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^a$ojaEu","text_ar":"الاَشْجَعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahoru","text_ar":"الدَّهْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fortune;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; and J says that this is what the poet means by the expression,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu A^ax~aA*N","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ اَخَّاذٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": but this cannot be the correct meaning, for the poet, namely El-Aashà, says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"biA^a$ojaEa A^ax~aA*K EalaY Ald~ahori Hukomuhu"},{"kind":"text","text":"by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA$jE","text_ar":"الاشجع"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning himself, or some other thing. (TA.)       -A2-  Also, (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i$ojaEN","text_ar":"اـِشْجَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or the latter accord. to some, but this was not known to Abu-l-Ghowth, (S,) sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAjiEu","text_ar":"اَشَاجِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [in some copies of the S written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAjiyEu","text_ar":"اَشَاجِيعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the former, which, as is mentioned in the TA, is found in the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1509},{"kind":"text","text":"handwriting of J, is that which is commonly known,] which signifies [The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knuckles nearest to the wrist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"this being what is meant by] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bases"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSuwl","text_ar":"اُصُول"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fingers, which are connected with the tendons of the outer side of the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) in the T, we find the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heads"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruw^uws","text_ar":"رُوُوس"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fingers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ASwl","text_ar":"اصول"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$jE","text_ar":"اشجع"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the hand and foot [but see what follows] signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tendons extended above the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulaAmaY","text_ar":"سُلَامَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[here meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"metacarpal and metatarsal bones"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the wrist to the bases"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uSuwl","text_ar":"اُصُول"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the fingers"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"toes, which are called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTonaAbu AlA^aSaAbiEi","text_ar":"اَطْنَابُ الاَصَابِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"above the outer side of the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bone which connects the finger with the wrist;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"metacarpal bone;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"every finger having to it a bone thus called:"},{"kind":"text","text":"he who says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$aAjiE","text_ar":"اَشَاجِع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so here instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A$jE","text_ar":"اشجع"},{"kind":"text","text":"as above] are the tendons calls those bones the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^usonaAE","text_ar":"اُسْنَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Aboo-Bekr is described as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAriY AlA^a$aAjiEi","text_ar":"عَارِى الاَشَاجِعِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano mafaASili AlA^aSaAbiEi","text_ar":"عَنْ مَفَاصِلِ الاَصَابِعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having little flesh upon what are thus termed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having their tendons apparent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAjibapN","text_ar":"رَاجِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"burojumapN","text_ar":"بُرْجُمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$ojaEu mino diykK","text_ar":"اَشْجَعُ مِنْ دِيكٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More courageous than a cock"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is one of the proverbs of the Arabs. (Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","IDrd","Msb"]}]}}